Variable_Name: Patient Number
Variable_Definition: Patient index

Variable_Name: SEXO (1-Hombre; 2-Mujer)
Variable_Definition: Patient sex

Variable_Name: Hospital de Procedencia
Variable_Definition: Hospital where patient was attended
Values: 1 (Hospital A); 2 (Hospital B) or 2 (Hospital C); NA (Missing value)

Variable_Name: Empeoramiento clínico después del TC (0-no; 1-empeora a causa del hematoma; 2-muere a causa del hematoma; 3-empeora por otra causa derivada). Tener en cuenta los quirúrgicos en el análisis
Variable_Definition: Patient follow up during hospitalization
Values: 0 (No deterioration after admission); 1 (Patient deterioration due to the hemorrhage); 2 (Patient death due to the hemorrhage); 3 (Patient deterioration but not due to the hemorrhage); NA (Missing value)

Variable_Name: Secuelas (0-no; 1-si; 2-si muere a causa del hematoma; 3-muere a causa de otra complicación; 4-le dan el alta y muere en los siguientes 3 meses por el hematoma). De momento todo se considera secuela (cuadrantanopsias;...)
Variable_Definition: Patient final outcome
Values: 0 (Complete curation); 1 (Curation with sequelae); 2 (Hospitalization death due to ICH); 3 (Hospitalization death but not due to ICH); 4 (Death in the next three months after hospital discharge due to ICH); NA (Missing value)

Variable_Name: Número de AP
Variable_Definition: Number of family relevant medical history events

Variable_Name: Fumador (0 - no; 1 - sí; 2 - exfumador; 1234 - sin datos)
Variable_Definition: Patient smoked tobacco
Values: 0 (Patient has never been a tobacco smoker); 1(Patient is currently a tobacco smoker); 2 (Patient is a past tobacco smoker); NA (Missing value)

Variable_Name: Fumador (paquetes/año: cigarrillos día/20 x años que lleva fumando; 1234 si no hay datos)
Variable_Definition: Packs years (cigarrettes per day/20 x years of tobacco use)

Variable_Name: Drogas (0 - no o no consta; 1 - cocaína; 2 - THC; 3 - otras; 4 - Exconsumidor)

Variable_Name: Alcohol (0 - no o no consta; 1 - sí; pero consumo habitual; 2 - sí; alcoholismo; 3 - exbebedor)
Variable_Definition: Alcohol consumption
Values: 0 (No drinking); 1 (Drink in moderation); 2 (Heavy drinking); 3 (Past heavy drinking)

Variable_Name: Alcohol (g/día; mL de bebida diaria x graduación x 0.8 / 100; 1234 si no consta)
Variable_Definition: Grammes of alcohol intake per day (mL x measured as a percentage x 0.8/100)

Variable_Definition: Idiopathic intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) / Primary intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) / Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) in hypertensive or amyloid angiopathy locations

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe) [Causa tratable: aneurisma y MAV; o secundaria a cualquier malformación vascular (aneurisma; MAV; cavernoma (39)..;)]
Variable_Definition: Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) caused by a vascular malformation (aneurysm; arteriovenous malformation; cavernoma...)

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe) [Traumatismo]
Variable_Definition: Traumatic intracranial hemorrhage (ICH)

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe) [Aneurisma]

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe) [MAV]
Variable_Definition: Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) caused by an arteriovenous malformation (AVM)

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - TH (no fibrinolisis ni trombectomía); 2 - Postfibrinolisis (post-IAMCEST; TEP u otro procedimiento no neurointervencionista); 3 - TH / Postfibrinolisis; 4 - TH/ Postrombectomía; 5 - TH / Post-fibrinolisis / post-trombectomí
Variable_Definition: Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) caused by an hemorrhagic transformation of a ischaemic brain infarct (HTI)
Values: 0 (No); 1 (HTI in a patient who have not undergone interventional procedures); 2 (HTI + non stroke fibrinolysis - myocardial infarction...); 3 (HTI + stroke fibrinolysis); 4 (HTI + trombectomy); 5 (HTI + stroke fibrinolysis + trombectomy)

Variable_Name: Causa del sangrado (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe) [Otra causa: paciente 178 - embolismos sépticos y tratamiento anticoagulante; 185 - Infarto hemorrágico post-trombosis senos SS y SGD; 260 - Hemorrgia tras trombosis SS; ST y SGD]
Variable_Definition: Intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) caused by other causes (bleeding after cerebral venous sinus thrombosis; septic cerebral emboli with bleeding)

Variable_Name: Neurocirugía (0 - no; 1 - sí; 2 - VDVP; 1234 - no se sabe)
Variable_Definition: The intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) has been treated with neurosurgery

Variable_Name: Intervencionismo (0 - no; 1 - sí; 1234 - no se sabe)

Variable_Name: Time between head CT scan and blood analysis (days)
Variable_Definition: Time passed between the performance of the head-CT scan and the blood analysis (days)
Comment: Values can be negative if blood analysis was prior to the head-CT scan. This variable was not collected; it was calculated by subtracting date_blooda from date_ct.

Variable_Name: Age at the hospital admission date (years)
Variable_Definition: Patient age at the hospital admission date (years)
Comment: This variable was not collected; it was calculated from date_adm and date_birth.

Variable_Name: Survival days after admission (days)
Variable_Definition: Total survival days after admission date (days)
Comment: This variable was not collected; it was calculated by subtracting date_adm from date_death (if patient still alive, the end of the study date - 2020-06-30 - is used as the death date).
